.TH "mutex_lock_killable" 9 "mutex_lock_killable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mutex_lock_killable \- Acquire the mutex, interruptible by fatal signals.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mutex_lock_killable
.BI "(struct mutex *lock "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "lock" 12
The mutex to be acquired.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Lock the mutex like \fBmutex_lock\fP.  If a signal which will be fatal to
the current process is delivered while the process is sleeping, this
function will return without acquiring the mutex.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Process context.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if the lock was successfully acquired or -EINTR if a
fatal signal arrived.
